full_text(utf-8): b"@forestminish such as the 2k sports games. or the battle royals to name a few. so overall what we see here is gameplay must be good but can be carried by a super engaging storyline with characters you can't walk away with. but we can have amazing gameplay and the story can still suck ->"

full_text: @Sparks_N_Zeros @sincespacies @Icaras011 @GwynCampbell i think their choice here basically puts the dividing line that this cartoon is a comedy while their live actions are serious. the art style itself has evolved from cartoon network and Nickelodeon as such its probably more appealing to those use to that style.
full_text(utf-8): b'@Sparks_N_Zeros @sincespacies @Icaras011 @GwynCampbell i think their choice here basically puts the dividing line that this cartoon is a comedy while their live actions are serious. the art style itself has evolved from cartoon network and Nickelodeon as such its probably more appealing to those use to that style.'

full_text:
@Sparks_N_Zeros @sincespacies @Icaras011 @GwynCampbell it reminds me of the art of final space. its an art form i don't mind but it fundamentally makes one statement. its a pure comedy.
if it was the detailed anime art then i'd be expecting a serious star trek show and at that point we'd have to ask why not live action then.
full_text(utf-8): b"@Sparks_N_Zeros @sincespacies @Icaras011 @GwynCampbell it reminds me of the art of final space. its an art form i don't mind but it fundamentally makes one statement. its a pure comedy.\nif it was the detailed anime art then i'd be expecting a serious star trek show and at that point we'd have to ask why not live action then."
